  "explanation": "The defendant is a first-time offender who committed a non-violent financial crime of $25,000, a significant portion of which has already been restituted. While embezzlement is a serious breach of trust, sentencing guidelines typically favor probation or short terms for amounts under $50,000 when the defendant has no record and shows remorse. The outburst from the spectator is irrelevant to the legal deliberations. A sentence of 6 months is sufficient as a punitive measure that allows for rehabilitation while reflecting the severity of the financial breach.",
  "verdict": 6
}
